      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Originalism is a judicial philosophy that asserts the Constitution should be interpreted based on the original understanding of its authors at the time it was adopted. This approach is grounded in the belief that the Constitution is a stable, enduring document that should not be subject to the whims of changing societal values or contemporary political agendas. Originalists argue that this method respects the democratic process, as it adheres to the intentions of the framers and the people who ratified it. They also contend that it provides a clear, objective standard for constitutional interpretation, preventing judges from imposing their personal biases or policy preferences on the law. This approach promotes legal certainty and predictability, ensuring that the Constitution remains a consistent guide for governance.",
